A suspected drug trafficker was arrested on Monday when a SARS customs officer found 7 2kg of ephedrine valued at R2 16m in her baggage.Ephedrine is the principal ingredient in the manufacture of crystal methamphetamine known locally as tik. A female passenger made inquiries about the parcel and was taken for questioning before being placed under arrest by the South African Police Service said a statement from SARS.Then on Wednesday narcotic dogs reacted to a consignment of boxes. SARS said they contained a liquid which tested positively for ecstasy A total of 86 litres was discovered with an estimated street value of R2 150 000. Both consignments were en route from Nigeria. On Thursday almost 5kg of cannabis was confiscated from the luggage of a pedestrian entering South Africa at the Caledonspoort border post with Lesotho.